cooking brocoli yea i probly spelled brocoli wrong but whatever if i cook brocoli in boiling water do all the vitamins and stuff leave the brocoli what about if steamed steamed is the best way all the nutrients remain as well as color and crispness broccoli with garlic butter and cashews ingredients pounds fresh broccoli cut into bite size pieces cup butter tablespoon brown sugar tablespoons soy sauce teaspoons white vinegar teaspoon ground black pepper cloves garlic minced cup chopped salted cashews directions place the broccoli into a large pot with about inch of water in the bottom bring to a boil and cook for minutes or until tender but still crisp drain and arrange broccoli on a serving platter while the broccoli is cooking melt the butter in a small skillet over medium heat mix in the brown sugar soy sauce vinegar pepper and garlic bring to a boil then remove from the heat mix in the cashews and pour the sauce over the broccoli serve immediately Tofu Japanese cuisine Chili con carne Cuisine of the Philippines Haggis Barbecue Cantonese cuisine Vinegar Soul food Ketchup Jewish cuisine French fries Halva Mayonnaise Cajun cuisine Ramen Coffee Cuisine of Denmark Cuisine of Laos Rice pudding Hot dog Bengali cuisine Dumpling Sushi Turkish coffee Jiaozi Idli Soy milk Curry Tea Sauce German cuisine Soy sauce Cuisine of Brazil Hamburger Garlic Recipe Cuisine of Malaysia Nabemono Chile pepper Cooking weights and measures Cuisine of Singapore Peanut butter Chocolate Tortilla Porridge Ice cream Bacon French cuisine Vitamin C Bearnaise sauce Chowder Pasta Fish and chips Rum Peanut Breakfast Cheese Worcestershire sauce Cuisine of Africa Gumbo Buffalo wings Food preservation Starch Cuisine of the Southern United States B__chamel sauce Mashed potato Cincinnati chili Common bean Brewery Ham Russian cuisine Menudo (soup) Rice Dim sum Cha chaan teng Soup Beef noodle soup Pancake Sugar beet Volume Bagel Cashew Magnesium Meatball Phosphorus Kelantan Donburi Egg (food) 